data.name: CapabilitiesInNonConforming
data.value: The CapabilitiesIn XML MUST conform to the API capClient schema.

data.name: DataObjectTypeNotSupported
data.value: In WMLS_AddToStore, the objectType being added in WMLtypeIn must be an objectType supported by the server. The server does not support the object type trying to be added.

data.name: DataObjectTypesDontMatch
data.value: In WMLS_AddToStore, the WMLtypeIn objectType must match the XMLin objectType. Currently, they do not match.

data.name: DataObjectUidAlreadyExists
data.value: For WMLS_AddToStore, a data-object with the same type and unique identifier(s) must NOT already exist in the persistent store

data.name: DataVersionNotSupported
data.value: For WMLS_GetCap, the OptionsIn keyword ‘dataVersion’ must specify a Data Schema Version that is supported by the server as defined by WMLS_GetVersion.

data.name: MissingClientUserAgent

data.name: InvalidKeywordValue
data.value: The value specified with an OptionsIn keyword must be a recognized value for that keyword.

data.name: KeywordNotSupportedByFunction
data.value: The OptionsIn value must be a recognized keyword for that function.

data.name: KeywordNotSupportedByServer
data.value: A client must not specify an OptionsIn keyword that is not supported by the server.

data.name: IncorrectCaseParentUid
data.value: Incorrect case on parent uid.

data.name: InputTemplateMultipleDataObjects
data.value: The input template must not specify more than one data-object.

data.name: InputTemplateNonConforming
data.value: The input template must conform to the appropriate derived schema.

data.name: MissingDataVersion
data.value: For WMLS_GetCap, the OptionsIn keyword ‘dataVersion’ must be specified.

data.name: MissingInputTemplate
data.value: A non-empty value must be defined for the input template.

data.name: MissingParentDataObject
data.value: Parent does not exist

data.name: MissingPluralRootElement
data.value: The input template MUST contain a plural root element.

data.name: MissingUnitForMeasureData
data.value: For WMLS_AddToStore and WMLS_UpdateInStore, the client must always specify the unit for all measure data.

data.name: MissingWmlTypeIn
data.value: A non-empty value must be defined for WMLtypeIn.

data.name: ParametersNotEncodedByRules
data.value: The OptionsIn parameter string must be encoded utilizing a subset (semicolon separators and no whitespace) of the encoding rules for HTML form content type application/x-www-form-urlencoded.

data.name: ParialSuccess
data.value: Partial success: Function completed successfully but some growing data-object data-nodes were not returned.

data.name: Success
data.value: Function completed successfully

data.name: MissingDataSchemaVersion
data.value: A QueryIn template must include a version attribute in the plural data-object that defines the Data Schema Version of the data-object.

data.name: ApiVersionNotSupported
data.value: The server does not support the API Version provided by the client.

data.name: InvalidClientSchemaVersion
data.value: In the value of the capClient schemaVersion, the oldest Data Schema Version must be listed first, followed by the next oldest, etc.

data.name: InvalidMaxReturnNodes
data.value: The value of the OptionsIn keyword of ‘maxReturnNodes’ MUST be greater than zero.

data.name: MissingDefaultWitsmlNamespace
data.value: A template must include a default namespace declaration for the WITSML namespace.

data.name: MissingElementUidForAdd
data.value: For WMLS_AddToStore, all parentage-pointers and lower level (child) uid values must be defined in the XMLin.

data.name: MissingRequiredData
data.value: A mandatory write schema item is missing.

data.name: ApiVersionNotMatch
data.value: The capClient apiVers value must match the API schema version.

data.name: SchemaVersionNotMatch
data.value: For the capClient object, the values of schemaVersion must match the version attribute used in the plural data-objects.

data.name: RecurringItemsEmptySelection
data.value: When multiple selection criteria is are included in a recurring pattern, an empty value must not be specified.

data.name: RecurringItemsInconsistentSelection
data.value: When multiple selection criteria is are included in a recurring element, the same selection items must exist in each recurring node.

data.name: QueryNotSupported
data.value: Query not supported.

data.name: QueryTemplateNonConforming
data.value: The query template is does not conform to the data schema for this data-object.

data.name: UpdateTemplateNonConforming
data.value: The XMLin document does not comply with the update schema.

data.name: InvalidMinimumQueryTemplate
data.value: If the OptionsIn keyword ‘requestObjectSelectionCapability’ is specified with a value other than ‘none’ then QueryIn must be the Minimum Query Template

data.name: InvalidOptionForChangeLogOnly
data.value: OptionsIn keyword returnsElements=latest-change-only can only be used for a changeLog object.

data.name: InvalidOptionForGrowingObjectOnly
data.value: The OptionsIn keyword ‘returnElements’ must not specify a value of “header-only” or “data-only” for a non-growing data-object.

data.name: InvalidOptionsInCombination
data.value: The OptionsIn keyword ‘requestObjectSelectionCapability’ with a value other than ‘none’ must not be specified with any other OptionsIn keyword.

data.name: ChildUidNotUnique
data.value: Each lower level child uid value must be unique within the context of its nearest recurring parent node.

data.name: InputDataObjectNotCompliant
data.value: The result of an add, update, or delete operation must be compliant with the derived write schema after performing a retrieval of the complete data-object

data.name: InvalidUnitOfMeasure
data.value: The value of the uom attribute is must match an ‘annotation’ attribute from the WITSML Units Dictionary XML file.

data.name: BadColumnIdentifier
data.value: For systematically growing data-objects, the column-identifier (mnemonic) values must not contain one of the following special characters: single-quote, double-quote, less than, greater than, forward slash, backward slash, ampersand, comma.

data.name: MixedStructuralRangeIndices
data.value: For growing data-objects, a combination of depth and date-time structural-range indices must not be specified.

data.name: IndexNotFirstInDataColumnList
data.value: If a column-identifier representing the index column is specified then it must be specified first in the data-column-list.

data.name: IndexCurveNotFound
data.value: When updating data in a systematically growing data-object the indexCurve must be specified in the mnemonicList.

data.name: DuplicateColumnIdentifiers
data.value: When adding or updating curves, column-identifiers must be unique.

data.name: MaxDataExceeded
data.value: The client must not attempt to add or update more data than is allowed by the server’s maxDataNodes and maxDataPoints values.

data.name: NodesWithSameIndex
data.value: For updating systematically growing data, the update data must not contain multiple nodes with the same index.

data.name: AddingUpdatingLogCurveAtTheSameTime
data.value: A new column(log curve) cannot be added at the same time an existing column(log curve) is being updated. (The index column (curve) does not count as being updated.)

data.name: DataObjectNotExist
data.value: A data-object with the same type and unique identifier(s) must already exist in the persistent store.

data.name: DataObjectUidMissing
data.value: The input template must specify the unique identifiers of one data-object to be processed.

data.name: EmptyNewElementsOrAttributes
data.value: For WMLS_UpdateInStore, new elements or attributes must not be empty.

data.name: IndexRangeSpecified
data.value: When an update adds a new column-identifier to a systematically growing data-object, a structural-range must not also be specified.

data.name: MissingColumnIdentifiers
data.value: For updating systematically growing data, if data-nodes are specified then the column-identifiers (mnemonic) must be specified in the data-column-list.

data.name: MissingElementUidForUpdate
data.value: For WMLS_UpdateInStore, if an element with a unique identifier in the schema is specified then the identifier value must also be specified

data.name: MissingUnitList
data.value: When updating data in a systematically growing data-object, the unitList must always be specified.

data.name: MnemonicsNotUnique
data.value: When updating data in a systematically growing data-object, each mnemonic must occur only once in the mnemonicList.

data.name: UnitListNotMatch
data.value: When updating data in a systematically growing data-object, the unitList must be populated with units that match the header.

data.name: DuplicateMnemonics
data.value: Duplicate mnemonics in a query are not allowed.

data.name: RecurringLogData
data.value: For WMLS_GetFromStore, the logData section must not recur when retrieving data.

data.name: ColumnIdentifiersNotSame
data.value: For getting systematically growing data-objects, if column-identifiers (mnemonics) are specified in both the header and data sections then the column-identifiers must be the same in the two sections.

data.name: MissingColumnDescriptionOrDataSection
data.value: For getting systematically growing data-objects, both column-description and data sections must be specified.

data.name: MissingMnemonicElement
data.value: For getting systematically growing data-objects, if a column-definition (logCurveInfo) section is specified then a mnemonic element must be specified.

data.name: MissingMnemonicList
data.value: For getting systematically growing data-objects, if a data-node (logData) section is specified then a mnemonicList element must be specified.

data.name: MissingSubsetOfGrowingDataObject
data.value: No subset of a growing data-object is specified.A query must specify a subset of one growing data-object per query, but multiple individual queries may be included inside the query plural data-object.

data.name: ErrorTransactionTimeout
data.value: Transaction timeout error

data.name: MissingMeasureDataForUnit
data.value: For WMLS_UpdateInStore, a uom attribute must not be specified unless its corresponding value is specified.

data.name: ErrorMaxDocumentSizeExceeded
data.value: Maximum document size exceeded

data.name: InvalidReturnValueIn
data.value: For WMLS_GetBaseMsg, a non-empty value must be specified for ReturnValueIn.

data.name: CannotDecompressQuery
data.value: Unable to decompress query.

data.name: ColumnIdentifierSpecified
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore with a systematically growing data-object, a column-identifier must not be specified in the data-column-list (mnemonicList).

data.name: CompressedInputNonConforming
data.value: The input template must conform to the appropriate derived schema after uncompressing the string.

data.name: DataItemNotSupported
data.value: A client must specify an item for data-item selection that the server supports.

data.name: DataObjectItemNotSupported
data.value: A client must specify an item (element or attribute) for data-object selection that the server supports.

data.name: EmptyElementNonConforming
data.value: A template containing empty values must otherwise conform to the appropriate derived schema.

data.name: EmptyMandatoryNodeSpecified
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, an empty node must not be specified for a non-recurring element or attribute that is mandatory in the write schema.

data.name: EmptyNonRecurringElementSpecified
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, an empty non-recurring container-element with no unique identifier in the schema or an empty value for logData must not be specified.

data.name: EmptyUidSpecified
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, an empty uid attribute must not be specified.

data.name: EmptyUomSpecified
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, an empty uom attribute must not be specified.

data.name: IndexDataUomNotSame
data.value: For a particular WMLS_AddToStore call, a client must specify all growing data-object index data in the same unit of measure.

data.name: InsufficientOperationRights
data.value: In the server configuration for the site, the user must have rights to perform the requested operation on the data-object.

data.name: MissingElementUidForDelete
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, if an element with a uid attribute in the schema is specified then it must also be specified with a value for its uid attribute.

data.name: MustRetainOneRecurringNode
data.value: For WMLS_DeleteFromStore, a recurring element that is mandatory in the write schema must retain at least one occurrence after the deletion.

data.name: NodeIndexNotSpecified
data.value: For growing data-objects in a query, if a node-index value is to be returned, then the client must explicitly specify it in the query(which is true for any element or attribute in a query).

data.name: NotBottomLevelDataObject
data.value: If cascading deletes are not invoked, a client must only request deletion of bottom level data-objects such that all child data-objects are deleted before the parent is deleted.

data.name: PollingTooFast
data.value: The client is polling too fast.

data.name: Unset
data.value: Unset

data.name: WellDatumNotSame
data.value: All datum elements or attributes for indexes in a growing data-object must implicitly or explicitly point to the same wellDatum when adding or updating data.

data.name: DataObjectNotSupported
data.value: The data-object must be supported by the server as defined in its capability data-object.

data.name: ErrorRowDataCount
data.value: Number of data values per row does not match number of column-identifiers (mnemonics).

data.name: PartialSuccessWithWarnings
data.value: Partial success: Function completed successfully with warnings, but some growing data-object data-nodes were not returned.

data.name: SuccessWithWarnings
data.value: Function completed successfully with warnings.

data.name: ErrorDeletingIndexCurve
data.value: When deleting log curves, index curve/data cannot be deleted without all other log curve/data are being deleted.

data.name: ErrorDeletingSimpleContent
data.value: When deleting simple content that has attribute(s), the attribute(s) should not be specified.

data.name: InvalidLogCurveInfoColumnIndex
data.value: The maximum columnIndex value was greater than the logData array length.

data.name: ErrorReplacingInDataStore
data.value: Error replacing data in data store

data.name: InvalidRequestLatestValue
data.value: The value of the OptionsIn keyword of ‘requestLatestValue’ MUST be greater than zero and less than or equal to the MaxRequestLatestValue.

data.name: InvalidOptionForMudLogObjectOnly
data.value: For WMLS_GetFromStore, the OptionsIn keyword ‘intervalRangeInclusion’ may only be used on a mudlog data-object.
